My dot vim to develop application. Tested on Linux. Inspired by http://github.com/xinuc/dotvim

Usage:
1. Clone this repo into your home directory either as .vim (linux/mac) or 
vimfiles (Windows):
git clone git://github.com/kuntoaji/slackvim.git ~/.vim

2. Then 'cd' into the repo and run this to get the snippets submodule:
git submodule init
git submodule update

3. Copy as _vimrc (Windows) in your home directory. In Mac or Linux, the 
easiest thing to do is create symbolic link:
% ln -s ~/.vim/vimrc ~/.vimrc

Example (I love gvim):
% gvim example.txt

Shorcuts in command mode:
1. Press Shift + Tab to toggle NERD_tree
2. Tab navigation: Ctrl+h, Ctrl+j, Ctrl+k, Ctrl+l
6. ,,p = paste from clipboard

Available colorscheme:
1. http://www.vi-improved.org/color_sampler_pack/
2. twilight2
3. ir_dark
